From: Yazen Ghannam <yazen.ghannam@amd.com>
Date: Thu, 30 Jan 2025 19:48:55 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] x86/amd_node, platform/x86/amd/hsmp: Have HSMP use SMN
 through AMD_NODE
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
References: bsc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 6.14.8
Git-commit: 735049b801cf3d597752017385cfc8768ce44303

[ Upstream commit 735049b801cf3d597752017385cfc8768ce44303 ]

The HSMP interface is just an SMN interface with different offsets.

Define an HSMP wrapper in the SMN code and have the HSMP platform driver
use that rather than a local solution.

Also, remove the "root" member from AMD_NB, since there are no more
users of it.

